<section class="what-it-is" id="about">
  <div class="container container-narrow">
    <h2 class="section-title text-center">What Rosemary Dream Is</h2>
    <p class="lead text-center text-muted">
      A co-investment opportunity shaped by three commitments.
    </p>

    <div class="overview-narrative">
      <p>
        Rosemary Dream is a 70,000-square-meter property on the jungle hillside of
        Florianópolis, Brazil. We are inviting a small group of aligned investors to
        co-own it together, build it out over time, and activate it as a living, working
        village and hospitality destination.
      </p>
      <p>
        The main value here is not only financial. It is relational and mission-driven.
        You are not buying into a passive vehicle. You are becoming a steward of a place
        with genuine community, a conservation commitment, and a specific vision for
        how people can work and live well together.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="pillars-grid">
      <div class="pillar-card">
        <span class="pillar-icon">🌿</span>
        <h3 class="pillar-title">Conservation-First Land</h3>
        <p class="pillar-description">
          Over 90% of the land is intended for conservation. Trails run through Atlantic
          Forest, past waterfalls, and through to the ocean on the other side of the ridge.
          This land is held as stewardship, not development.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="pillar-card">
        <span class="pillar-icon">🏘️</span>
        <h3 class="pillar-title">Seasonal Village of Impact</h3>
        <p class="pillar-description">
          Three months per year, typically December through February, the property runs as
          a gathering of aligned individuals working on projects that matter. Structured,
          purposeful, and genuinely alive.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="pillar-card">
        <span class="pillar-icon">🌊</span>
        <h3 class="pillar-title">Year-Round Hospitality, Retreats, and Residencies</h3>
        <p class="pillar-description">
          The rest of the year, the property earns through curated hospitality stays,
          focused retreats, and impact residencies centered on human and environmental
          flourishing.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

